Jeff Atwood, of Coding Horror fame, wrote a blogpost called &ldquo;Why Can&rsquo;t Programmers.. Program?&rdquo;, by a happy coincidence nearly exactly 10 years ago.
Central to the post is the assertion that candidates for development jobs should be initially screened on tasks that any remotely experienced programmer might (many would say should) consider low hanging fruit, the canonical example offered being &ldquo;FizzBuzz.&rdquo;
